properties in an LLC?

00:51:39.020 --> 00:51:42.030
I can tell you I personally
do hold them in an LLC,

00:51:42.030 --> 00:51:43.734
but I can't say that
that's necessarily

00:51:43.734 --> 00:51:44.900
the best thing for everyone.

00:51:44.900 --> 00:51:46.270
There are a lot of
different things.

00:51:46.270 --> 00:51:48.140
So we have to, you know,
use the disclaimer,

00:51:48.140 --> 00:51:50.640
talk to your lawyer, find
out what works for them.

00:51:50.640 --> 00:51:54.160
But my lawyer told
me an LLC works well.

00:51:54.160 --> 00:51:57.110
JOSH: And I'm again not
going to tell you what to do.

00:51:57.110 --> 00:52:00.190
But some people will hold
single properties in an LLC.

00:52:00.190 --> 00:52:03.630
Some people will take an LLC
for all their A-type properties,

00:52:03.630 --> 00:52:05.310
take another LLC for
all their B-type,

00:52:05.310 --> 00:52:07.810
another LLC per partnership.

00:52:07.810 --> 00:52:10.770
Or they'll do-- I mean,
there's a million things

00:52:10.770 --> 00:52:11.982
that you really can do.

00:52:11.982 --> 00:52:13.815
But again, you want to
talk to your attorney

00:52:13.815 --> 00:52:15.270
and your accountant
to figure out

00:52:15.270 --> 00:52:18.930
what the best structure
for yourself is.

